29
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:46,960
It went viral.

30
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:51,360
All of this was happening in my final year of university, this was just like a side project,

31
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:51,520
right?

32
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:54,880
I was happy it made money, but I'm not going to drop out yet.

33
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:59,439
But when I saw the first sale and then like it kept going and like this is this is significant.

34
00:01:59,439 --> 00:02:03,360
I had like two or three sales every day and uh I dropped out.

35
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:03,680
All right.

36
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:06,880
So, you mentioned that you tweeted something out to your 16 followers.

37
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:11,680
It went viral and essentially that this this one tweet kind of changed your life.

38
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:14,239
Can you walk me through this viral tweet?

39
00:02:14,239 --> 00:02:17,680
I think this was like my third tweet ever in my life.

40
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:20,480
For this one, three things made it work well.

41
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:26,319
One, a familiar interface, the streaming interface where like the text is streaming uh in a in like a chat interface.

42
00:02:26,319 --> 00:02:30,800
Yeah, this was like a very chat GPT thing which like at the time was going viral.

43
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,519
So, I think taking a glance at the demo, it's just just interesting.

44
00:02:33,519 --> 00:02:37,840
The other part was minimizing the seconds to like the aha moment.

45
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,360
I think I did that well here.

46
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,120
Like it's a very simple demo, right?

47
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:46,000
But it just shows you exactly what I built was capable of in like the first 20 seconds,

48
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:46,319
right?

49
00:02:46,319 --> 00:02:51,120
And I think the other thing I did is mention the tools that I was using 2 and a half years ago.

50
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:54,400
Like there was a bunch of new AI companies, AI tools starting out.

51
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,720
No one had any customers because they're all new.

52
00:02:56,720 --> 00:03:04,319
So every company was trying to show people like, hey, this is something that is being used by real people building like real products.

53
00:03:04,319 --> 00:03:15,840
When I mentioned like Langchin and Pine Cone and stuff like that, it made sense for them to push it too because no one else was building stuff like this on their platforms yet because it was all very new and they they wanted to promote like their AI features and stuff like that.

54
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:19,120
When I mentioned this, those people picked it up and they were like going viral.

55
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:26,800
So my thing also went viral and then it created this viral loop and I think yeah most of most of the initial traction was from that.

56
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,959
I really do like the kind of build in public thing that you're doing.

57
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:32,560
You're kind of sharing what tools you were using and that was a big piece in it.

58
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:36,720
if you could break down the build in public playbook because I know you kind of did this over and over again.

59
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:38,799
Tell me what you learned and and what works there.

60
00:03:38,799 --> 00:03:43,760
Yeah, so I think the easiest thing is just to share what you're doing every day.

61
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:45,760
That's like the most basic thing you can do.

62
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:51,200
First two or 3 months if you're if you're not lucky, it will just be you practicing what works and what doesn't.

63
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:54,720
It's it's not going to get any any views because you're you're trying to build a brand,

64
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:57,200
